        <p>The worst case approach is useful when a conservative estimate of fire hazard and risk is appropriate or when the user is interested in identifying high fire hazard situations during wind-driven wildfires.</p>
        <p>In the future, this tool will also be useful for assessing the effectiveness of a fuel treatment at reducing the hazard of a fire burning as a head fire.</p>
